1
00:00:02.439 --> 00:00:06.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
SISKO: <i>Captain's Personal Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 51247.5.</i>

2
00:00:06.357 --> 00:00:09.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It's been a week since</i>
<i>our return to Deep Space 9,</i>

3
00:00:09.476 --> 00:00:11.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>but the mood</i>
<i>of celebration continues.</i>

4
00:00:11.955 --> 00:00:13.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We're still at war,</i>
<i>and the station's</i>

5
00:00:13.875 --> 00:00:15.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>been designated headquarters</i>
<i>for the Ninth Fleet.</i>

6
00:00:15.954 --> 00:00:17.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That, plus</i>
<i>our strategic position</i>

7
00:00:17.993 --> 00:00:19.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>guarding the wormhole,</i>
<i>makes DS9</i>

8
00:00:20.734 --> 00:00:21.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>one of the most</i>
<i>tempting targets</i>

9
00:00:21.672 --> 00:00:23.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>in the entire quadrant.</i>

10
00:00:23.312 --> 00:00:26.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But for now, at least,</i>
<i>the war seems very far away.</i>

11
00:00:33.229 --> 00:00:34.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Morning.
-Good morning.

12
00:00:34.708 --> 00:00:35.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good morning.

13
00:00:35.948 --> 00:00:37.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Morning, Major.

14
00:00:37.268 --> 00:00:39.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good morning, Captain.

15
00:00:39.107 --> 00:00:40.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know
how much I missed

16
00:00:40.667 --> 00:00:41.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
hearing you say that?

17
00:00:42.269 --> 00:00:43.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know how much
I hated saying

18
00:00:44.259 --> 00:00:45.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Good morning, Dukat"?

19
00:00:45.105 --> 00:00:45.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can imagine.

20
00:00:46.652 --> 00:00:47.385 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's on the agenda?

21
00:00:47.465 --> 00:00:50.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh, USS <i>Potemkin</i>
has completed her repairs

22
00:00:50.184 --> 00:00:52.143 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and is rejoining the fleet
later today.

23
00:00:52.224 --> 00:00:53.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Exeter, Sutherland</i>
and <i>Agaki</i>

24
00:00:53.863 --> 00:00:55.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
have submitted
resupply requests

25
00:00:55.702 --> 00:00:57.502 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and there are
about 1,000 messages

26
00:00:57.582 --> 00:00:58.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
from Starfleet Command

27
00:00:58.981 --> 00:01:00.781 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
awaiting your "eyes-only"
attention.

28
00:01:00.861 --> 00:01:02.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Anything else?

29
00:01:02.260 --> 00:01:04.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
General Martok is waiting
in your office.

30
00:01:04.380 --> 00:01:06.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, I'll start
with the General.

31
00:01:06.179 --> 00:01:07.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought you would.

32
00:01:09.658 --> 00:01:12.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have I mentioned
that it's good to be home?

33
00:01:13.577 --> 00:01:15.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Once or twice.

34
00:01:17.559 --> 00:01:18.656 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

35
00:01:22.334 --> 00:01:24.534 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You knew about this,
didn't you?

36
00:01:24.613 --> 00:01:26.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I had a pretty good idea.

37
00:01:26.214 --> 00:01:29.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you did nothing to stop it.

38
00:01:29.931 --> 00:01:30.572 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

39
00:01:30.652 --> 00:01:33.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In fact, I recommended you
for the position myself.

40
00:01:33.411 --> 00:01:35.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Allow me to offer
my congratulations

41
00:01:35.651 --> 00:01:37.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to the new
Supreme Commander

42
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:38.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
of the Ninth Fleet.

43
00:01:40.890 --> 00:01:42.249 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you have any idea
how much paperwork

44
00:01:42.328 --> 00:01:44.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a Supreme Commander
has to do?

45
00:01:44.528 --> 00:01:45.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're welcome.

46
00:01:45.568 --> 00:01:47.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>growls </i>)

47
00:01:47.687 --> 00:01:49.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
May I arrange quarters
for you on the station?

48
00:01:49.527 --> 00:01:52.885 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, I'll keep my flag
aboard the <i>Rotarran.</i>

49
00:01:52.966 --> 00:01:56.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It may be cramped but at least I'll feel
like I'm still in the war.

50
00:01:56.444 --> 00:01:59.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
By the way, I'd like Worf
to continue functioning

51
00:01:59.404 --> 00:02:01.123 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
as my principal
Intelligence Officer.

52
00:02:01.202 --> 00:02:03.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't see any problem
with that.

53
00:02:03.122 --> 00:02:05.962 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's the only officer I know
who can never get enough work.

54
00:02:06.415 --> 00:02:07.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>cackles </i>)

55
00:02:08.127 --> 00:02:09.480 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, at least if he's busy

56
00:02:09.561 --> 00:02:12.519 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
he'll stop going on
about this wedding of his.

57
00:02:13.999 --> 00:02:16.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, there were times
aboard the <i>Rotarran</i>

58
00:02:16.158 --> 00:02:17.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
he nearly drove me mad.

59
00:02:17.957 --> 00:02:20.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Until his son arrived,
it was all he could talk about.

60
00:02:20.956 --> 00:02:23.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then Alexander became
all he could talk about.

61
00:02:23.796 --> 00:02:27.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The man is nothing
if not single-minded.

62
00:02:27.195 --> 00:02:28.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I haven't met Worf's son yet.

63
00:02:28.954 --> 00:02:30.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's he like?

64
00:02:30.914 --> 00:02:32.473 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's a fine boy...

65
00:02:32.554 --> 00:02:35.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
dedicated, eager.

66
00:02:35.112 --> 00:02:37.831 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He has the heart
of his father

67
00:02:37.912 --> 00:02:41.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but he's not the best
soldier I've ever seen.

68
00:02:41.311 --> 00:02:43.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But when he ordered me
to bring the system back online,

69
00:02:43.670 --> 00:02:44.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought he was still talking

70
00:02:45.302 --> 00:02:47.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
about the hydro-static
system, so...

71
00:02:47.509 --> 00:02:48.589 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You didn't
engage the pumps

72
00:02:48.668 --> 00:02:50.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
while the check valves
were open.

73
00:02:50.268 --> 00:02:51.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He did.

74
00:02:51.588 --> 00:02:53.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I flooded
the entire deck

75
00:02:53.467 --> 00:02:55.187 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
with super-heated
hydraulic fluid.

76
00:02:55.266 --> 00:02:57.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It took me three days
to clean it up

77
00:02:57.506 --> 00:03:00.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but, I swear, it still smells
like burnt dog hair in there.

78
00:03:00.225 --> 00:03:03.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh! Remind me to keep you away
from the <i>Defiant. </i>You're a menace.

79
00:03:03.544 --> 00:03:06.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The <i>Rotarran's </i>crew actually thinks of me
as a good luck charm.

80
00:03:06.543 --> 00:03:11.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, the more mistakes
<i>I </i>make, the safer <i>they </i>feel.

81
00:03:11.541 --> 00:03:13.860 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope the <i>Ya'Vang's crew</i>
feels the same way.

82
00:03:13.941 --> 00:03:15.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The <i>Ya'Vang?</i>

83
00:03:16.461 --> 00:03:18.579 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I got new orders this morning.

84
00:03:18.659 --> 00:03:21.179 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The battle cruiser <i>Ya'Vang</i>
took heavy losses

85
00:03:21.259 --> 00:03:22.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in their last engagement

86
00:03:22.978 --> 00:03:25.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so most of the <i>Rotarran's crew</i>
are being transferred there

87
00:03:25.338 --> 00:03:27.697 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
at the end of the week,
including me.

88
00:03:29.776 --> 00:03:32.964 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, more bloodwine?

89
00:03:32.176 --> 00:03:33.295 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why not?

90
00:03:33.375 --> 00:03:35.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No. Not for me.

91
00:03:37.148 --> 00:03:38.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Handsome young man.

92
00:03:38.733 --> 00:03:40.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He must get his looks
from his mother's side.

93
00:03:40.733 --> 00:03:42.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do you want?

94
00:03:42.292 --> 00:03:45.532 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have you had a chance
to reconsider my offer?

95
00:03:45.611 --> 00:03:48.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We are not getting
married in this bar.

96
00:03:48.610 --> 00:03:50.930 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The ceremony will take place
on the Klingon homeworld

97
00:03:51.107 --> 00:03:52.169 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
after the war.

98
00:03:52.250 --> 00:03:55.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Worf, let's do it here,
this week

99
00:03:55.209 --> 00:03:56.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before Alexander leaves.

100
00:03:56.528 --> 00:03:57.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
QUARK:
Perfect.

101
00:03:57.848 --> 00:03:59.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll handle
all the arrangements.

102
00:03:59.882 --> 00:04:01.606 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Wait. I thought
we had agreed.

103
00:04:01.687 --> 00:04:03.766 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We did, but I would hate
for Alexander

104
00:04:03.846 --> 00:04:04.926 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to miss
his father's wedding.

105
00:04:05.565 --> 00:04:07.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It would mean so much to him.

106
00:04:08.484 --> 00:04:11.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And besides,
it may be a long time

107
00:04:11.323 --> 00:04:13.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before you see him again.

108
00:04:18.761 --> 00:04:20.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's going on?

109
00:04:24.407 --> 00:04:25.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our wedding plans
have changed.

110
00:04:25.960 --> 00:04:28.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We are getting married here
on Deep Space 9

111
00:04:28.918 --> 00:04:32.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I would like you
to be my <i>Tawi'Yan.</i>

112
00:04:35.237 --> 00:04:37.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Sword-bearer."

113
00:04:37.116 --> 00:04:39.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's sort of like
a best man.

114
00:04:39.595 --> 00:04:41.595 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me?

115
00:04:41.675 --> 00:04:42.874 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really?

116
00:04:42.955 --> 00:04:43.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, that's great!

117
00:04:43.914 --> 00:04:45.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>yelping </i>)

118
00:04:47.673 --> 00:04:49.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll put that
on your tab.

119
00:06:45.918 --> 00:06:46.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
DAX:
It doesn't leave much time

120
00:06:46.957 --> 00:06:48.397 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to make
all the arrangements

121
00:06:48.476 --> 00:06:50.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but fortunately, there isn't
that much left to do.

122
00:06:50.476 --> 00:06:52.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Worf's been planning
the ceremony

123
00:06:52.275 --> 00:06:53.755 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
for the last three months.

124
00:06:53.835 --> 00:06:55.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
He has everything
figured out

125
00:06:55.635 --> 00:06:57.594 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
right down
to the color of my shoes.

126
00:06:57.674 --> 00:07:00.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
No offense, Jadzia,
but it seems like this wedding's

127
00:07:00.433 --> 00:07:01.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
all about what Worf wants.

128
00:07:02.327 --> 00:07:04.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Uh, Habitat Ring,
Section 51 Gamma.

129
00:07:04.712 --> 00:07:06.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What about you?

130
00:07:06.711 --> 00:07:09.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
A traditional Klingon wedding
with all the trimmings

131
00:07:09.190 --> 00:07:12.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
is something Worf's
been thinking about since he was a boy.

132
00:07:12.110 --> 00:07:14.509 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It probably has something
to do with being raised

133
00:07:14.589 --> 00:07:16.109 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
by human parents.

134
00:07:16.188 --> 00:07:18.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
In any case, when it comes
to Klingon tradition,

135
00:07:18.228 --> 00:07:19.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Worf is very sentimental.

136
00:07:19.388 --> 00:07:20.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Worf?

137
00:07:20.827 --> 00:07:22.786 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
All men are sentimental.

138
00:07:22.866 --> 00:07:26.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
They just cover it up with
scowls and clenched jaws.

139
00:07:26.345 --> 00:07:30.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
There are times when Worf
literally gets misty-eyed

140
00:07:30.784 --> 00:07:32.824 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
talking about
Klingon rituals.

141
00:07:34.235 --> 00:07:35.863 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
So, uh, that's
why you're letting him

142
00:07:35.942 --> 00:07:37.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
make the plans
for the wedding?

143
00:07:37.502 --> 00:07:39.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Mostly, but
the truth is

144
00:07:39.621 --> 00:07:40.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I've already
been through five

145
00:07:40.901 --> 00:07:41.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Trill ceremonies--

146
00:07:42.607 --> 00:07:43.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
three as a bride,
two as a groom,

147
00:07:43.620 --> 00:07:44.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
and I'm a little bored with it.

148
00:07:44.820 --> 00:07:46.597 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Is it my imagination

149
00:07:46.140 --> 00:07:47.739 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
or did Odo just
try and avoid us?

150
00:07:47.819 --> 00:07:49.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I didn't notice.

151
00:07:49.738 --> 00:07:50.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

152
00:07:50.898 --> 00:07:52.377 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
We've been avoiding
each other

153
00:07:52.457 --> 00:07:54.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
ever since the Dominion
left the station.

154
00:07:54.537 --> 00:07:56.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I think we're both
afraid of talking

155
00:07:56.969 --> 00:07:57.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
about what happened
during the occupation.

156
00:07:58.163 --> 00:08:00.295 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What do you mean?

157
00:08:00.375 --> 00:08:02.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Oh, to tell you the truth,

158
00:08:02.735 --> 00:08:05.493 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
it's nothing I want to talk
about right now either.

159
00:08:08.652 --> 00:08:09.972 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Thank you for coming.

160
00:08:10.525 --> 00:08:12.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
As you probably know by now,

161
00:08:12.918 --> 00:08:14.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Jadzia and I will be married
here on the station in six days.

162
00:08:14.891 --> 00:08:16.330 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's nothing
more romantic

163
00:08:16.410 --> 00:08:18.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
than a wedding on
DS9 in springtime.

164
00:08:18.649 --> 00:08:20.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When the neutrinos
are in bloom.

165
00:08:20.409 --> 00:08:23.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
By tradition,
the Klingon man spends

166
00:08:23.569 --> 00:08:24.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the four nights
before his wedding

167
00:08:24.888 --> 00:08:27.473 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
on a mental
and spiritual journey.

168
00:08:27.127 --> 00:08:30.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is called <i>Kal'Hyah,</i>
"The Path of Clarity"

169
00:08:30.287 --> 00:08:34.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and </i>he is accompanied
by his closest male friends.

170
00:08:34.165 --> 00:08:36.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You cannot imagine
the experience that awaits us--

171
00:08:36.604 --> 00:08:40.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
four long nights filled
with song and fellowship.

172
00:08:40.963 --> 00:08:43.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A time of unbridled pleasures.

173
00:08:43.282 --> 00:08:46.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are we talking
about a bachelor party here?

174
00:08:46.121 --> 00:08:48.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It is a similar ritual.

175
00:08:48.441 --> 00:08:49.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sounds good to me.

176
00:08:50.402 --> 00:08:51.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me, too.

177
00:08:51.480 --> 00:08:53.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Count me in.

178
00:08:53.160 --> 00:08:54.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We will meet
in the holosuite

179
00:08:54.639 --> 00:08:56.278 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
tomorrow night
at 2100 hours.

180
00:08:56.358 --> 00:08:58.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MARTOK: I advise you all
to get plenty of rest.

181
00:08:58.398 --> 00:09:00.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Four nights
at a Klingon bachelor party.

182
00:09:00.637 --> 00:09:02.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just think of
the possibilities.

183
00:09:02.156 --> 00:09:03.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thank God
Keiko's not here.

184
00:09:03.276 --> 00:09:04.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wonder what Dax
will be doing

185
00:09:04.636 --> 00:09:06.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
while we're traveling
down <i>Kal'Hyah.</i>

186
00:09:06.756 --> 00:09:09.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She will be taking
a different journey...

187
00:09:09.114 --> 00:09:11.153 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
with my wife.

188
00:09:12.393 --> 00:09:13.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your wife?

189
00:09:18.792 --> 00:09:19.991 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
By marrying Worf,

190
00:09:20.712 --> 00:09:22.712 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dax will be joining
the House of Martok.

191
00:09:22.150 --> 00:09:23.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Since the mistress
of a great House

192
00:09:23.870 --> 00:09:25.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
must approve all marriages,

193
00:09:25.470 --> 00:09:26.789 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sirella will spend
the next four days

194
00:09:26.869 --> 00:09:28.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
evaluating Jadzia.

195
00:09:36.386 --> 00:09:38.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My lady.

196
00:09:38.146 --> 00:09:40.785 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You've put on weight...

197
00:09:40.865 --> 00:09:43.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and your hair is going gray.

198
00:09:44.224 --> 00:09:48.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My deterioration
is proceeding apace.

199
00:09:48.943 --> 00:09:51.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought you would be
in your grave by now.

200
00:09:51.901 --> 00:09:52.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>chuckling </i>)

201
00:09:52.942 --> 00:09:54.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I shall endeavor to die--

202
00:09:54.821 --> 00:09:56.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
this year, if possible.

203
00:09:56.580 --> 00:09:59.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Allow me to present
Captain Benjamin Sisko,

204
00:09:59.339 --> 00:10:01.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander of Deep Space 9.

205
00:10:01.219 --> 00:10:03.991 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Captain, may I present

206
00:10:03.178 --> 00:10:05.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the mistress of the House
of Martok, my wife

207
00:10:05.978 --> 00:10:07.697 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the mother
of my children...

208
00:10:07.776 --> 00:10:10.256 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sirella, daughter of Linkasa.

209
00:10:10.336 --> 00:10:12.855 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Welcome to
Deep Space 9.

210
00:10:12.935 --> 00:10:14.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you, Captain.

211
00:10:15.155 --> 00:10:16.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where is she?

212
00:10:16.375 --> 00:10:18.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Jadzia's quarters
are in the Habitat Ring,

213
00:10:18.893 --> 00:10:21.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Section... 25 Alpha.

214
00:10:21.613 --> 00:10:22.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shall I escort you?

215
00:10:22.813 --> 00:10:24.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's quite far away.

216
00:10:24.292 --> 00:10:25.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll find my way.

217
00:10:29.210 --> 00:10:30.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you'll excuse me.

218
00:10:34.289 --> 00:10:37.486 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Magnificent, isn't she?

219
00:10:45.885 --> 00:10:48.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are those real
<i>var'Hama </i>candles?

220
00:10:48.725 --> 00:10:50.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes, Worf,
I traveled to Kronos.

221
00:10:50.884 --> 00:10:53.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I captured three <i>targs</i>
in the Hamar mountains,

222
00:10:53.803 --> 00:10:55.123 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
made the ritual
sacrifice at dawn,

223
00:10:55.203 --> 00:10:57.123 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
came back
to the station,

224
00:10:57.202 --> 00:10:59.241 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
asked Quark to boil their
shoulders into tallow.

225
00:10:59.321 --> 00:11:02.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then, I spent two days
molding them into candles

226
00:11:02.601 --> 00:11:03.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
with my own hands.

227
00:11:03.680 --> 00:11:05.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was just asking.

228
00:11:05.840 --> 00:11:09.159 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You were
criticizing <i>again.</i>

229
00:11:09.238 --> 00:11:11.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Relax. She's not
going to reject

230
00:11:11.797 --> 00:11:13.776 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a prospective daughter

231
00:11:13.158 --> 00:11:14.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because the
<i>var'Hama </i>candles

232
00:11:14.437 --> 00:11:15.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in her welcoming
display were replicated.

233
00:11:15.956 --> 00:11:16.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>door chimes </i>)

234
00:11:16.916 --> 00:11:18.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come in.

235
00:11:23.554 --> 00:11:26.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Tug son bosh mok</i>
<i>A'Beh, Sirella koH.</i>

236
00:11:26.513 --> 00:11:27.753 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>E'Gagh vet moh.</i>

237
00:11:28.873 --> 00:11:31.322 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is <i>he </i>doing here?

238
00:11:31.112 --> 00:11:32.991 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I meant no disrespect.

239
00:11:33.714 --> 00:11:34.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then leave.

240
00:11:42.428 --> 00:11:46.280 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your worthiness to join
our House will now be judged

241
00:11:46.107 --> 00:11:48.347 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
according to the traditions
of my family.

242
00:11:48.426 --> 00:11:49.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am prepared, my lady.

243
00:11:49.747 --> 00:11:51.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I doubt that.

244
00:11:51.585 --> 00:11:55.824 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A Klingon woman would find it
difficult to gain my favor.

245
00:11:55.905 --> 00:11:58.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
For...an <i>alien,</i>

246
00:11:58.504 --> 00:12:00.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it will most likely
be impossible.

247
00:12:00.703 --> 00:12:02.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I like a challenge.

248
00:12:02.262 --> 00:12:06.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I will not have my authority
challenged by you.

249
00:12:06.581 --> 00:12:08.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's not what I meant.

250
00:12:08.420 --> 00:12:11.340 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you cannot say what you mean,
say nothing at all.

251
00:12:12.780 --> 00:12:15.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The evaluation
will begin tomorrow morning.

252
00:12:15.578 --> 00:12:19.218 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have the traditional meal
prepared before I arrive.

253
00:12:21.177 --> 00:12:22.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And in the future,

254
00:12:22.816 --> 00:12:26.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if you cannot trouble yourself
to make real <i>var'Hama </i>candles,

255
00:12:26.535 --> 00:12:29.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
try not to use
such obvious fakes.

256
00:12:45.169 --> 00:12:47.689 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You never told me that your wife
was opposed to this marriage.

257
00:12:47.768 --> 00:12:49.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sirella is a woman
of strong convictions.

258
00:12:49.768 --> 00:12:51.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She believes
that by bringing aliens

259
00:12:51.568 --> 00:12:53.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
into our families,
we risk losing our identity

260
00:12:54.478 --> 00:12:55.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
as Klingons.

261
00:12:55.367 --> 00:12:57.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That is a prejudiced,
xenophobic view.

262
00:12:57.206 --> 00:12:59.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We <i>are </i>Klingons, Worf.

263
00:12:59.205 --> 00:13:02.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We don't <i>embrace </i>other cultures.
We <i>conquer </i>them.

264
00:13:02.845 --> 00:13:06.437 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If someone wishes to join us,
they must honor our traditions

265
00:13:06.124 --> 00:13:07.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and prove themselves worthy

266
00:13:07.763 --> 00:13:10.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of wearing the crest
of a Great House.

267
00:13:10.202 --> 00:13:11.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jadzia <i>is </i>worthy.

268
00:13:11.562 --> 00:13:13.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course she is.

269
00:13:13.402 --> 00:13:16.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She's an honorable woman
and a formidable warrior.

270
00:13:16.440 --> 00:13:18.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You should say <i>that </i>to Sirella.

271
00:13:20.396 --> 00:13:21.319 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's not such a good idea.

272
00:13:21.399 --> 00:13:23.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't want her to think

273
00:13:23.558 --> 00:13:27.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that I'm interfering
in her domain.

274
00:13:27.757 --> 00:13:29.837 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Perhaps I should
speak with her.

275
00:13:29.916 --> 00:13:32.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Coming from me, it would
not seem like a challenge

276
00:13:32.676 --> 00:13:33.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to her authority.

277
00:13:33.955 --> 00:13:35.595 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wouldn't do that
if I were you.

278
00:13:37.394 --> 00:13:38.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why?

279
00:13:39.593 --> 00:13:41.273 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, um...

280
00:13:41.353 --> 00:13:44.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the truth is...

281
00:13:44.112 --> 00:13:46.191 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
she doesn't like you
that much either.

282
00:13:46.272 --> 00:13:47.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me.

283
00:13:48.313 --> 00:13:49.950 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't let that
bother you.

284
00:13:50.304 --> 00:13:52.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I had every right
to bring you into the family

285
00:13:52.789 --> 00:13:54.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and she's accepted the fact

286
00:13:54.549 --> 00:13:57.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that there's <i>nothing</i>
she can do about it.

287
00:13:57.188 --> 00:13:58.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How comforting.

288
00:13:59.827 --> 00:14:00.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>chuckles </i>)

289
00:14:00.787 --> 00:14:03.786 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>laughing </i>)

290
00:14:03.866 --> 00:14:07.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And they say that
you have no sense of humor.

291
00:14:07.545 --> 00:14:10.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>laughing </i>)

292
00:14:24.100 --> 00:14:26.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Phew. I could do
without the heat.

293
00:14:26.499 --> 00:14:28.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can't, uh, say much
for the decor either.

294
00:14:29.593 --> 00:14:31.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, it can't be
<i>all </i>fun and games.

295
00:14:31.458 --> 00:14:34.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sure there has to be
some sort of ritual

296
00:14:34.657 --> 00:14:37.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we have to go through
before the party begins.

297
00:14:37.656 --> 00:14:40.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There <i>is </i>going to be
a party, isn't there?

298
00:14:40.535 --> 00:14:41.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're asking me?

299
00:14:42.552 --> 00:14:44.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can barely say
my name in Klingon.

300
00:14:44.974 --> 00:14:47.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MARTOK:
Prepare yourselves, my friends

301
00:14:47.813 --> 00:14:49.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
for a journey
you won't soon forget.

302
00:14:55.491 --> 00:14:56.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
These...

303
00:14:56.891 --> 00:14:58.290 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
are <i>Ma'Stakas.</i>

304
00:14:58.370 --> 00:15:00.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What, uh, what do
we do with them?

305
00:15:00.210 --> 00:15:02.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
At the conclusion
of the wedding ceremony

306
00:15:02.609 --> 00:15:04.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you will use them
to attack Worf and Dax.

307
00:15:04.968 --> 00:15:06.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Obviously.
Don't you know anything?

308
00:15:06.527 --> 00:15:07.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The tradition dates back

309
00:15:07.887 --> 00:15:09.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to the wedding
of Kahless and Lukara

310
00:15:09.807 --> 00:15:11.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who were nearly killed
by Molor's troops

311
00:15:11.486 --> 00:15:12.766 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
moments after they were
married.

312
00:15:12.845 --> 00:15:14.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Until the ceremony,

313
00:15:14.485 --> 00:15:15.844 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you should keep these with you
at all times.

314
00:15:15.925 --> 00:15:17.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
SISKO:
I trust

315
00:15:17.404 --> 00:15:19.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
this combat is non-lethal.

316
00:15:19.883 --> 00:15:22.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is a symbolic
attack only.

317
00:15:22.363 --> 00:15:23.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

318
00:15:25.562 --> 00:15:27.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That food is not
to be eaten.

319
00:15:29.200 --> 00:15:30.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then what is it for?

320
00:15:30.520 --> 00:15:33.319 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is there to tempt us
to break our fast.

321
00:15:33.399 --> 00:15:34.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fast?

322
00:15:34.639 --> 00:15:35.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There are six trials

323
00:15:35.998 --> 00:15:38.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we must face
on the path to <i>Kal'Hyah.</i>

324
00:15:38.477 --> 00:15:40.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is the first--
deprivation.

325
00:15:40.757 --> 00:15:42.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We now begin a fast
that will continue

326
00:15:42.876 --> 00:15:44.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
until the day of the wedding.

327
00:15:44.476 --> 00:15:46.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, th-that's
four days away.

328
00:15:46.276 --> 00:15:47.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MARTOK:
It is a short time,

329
00:15:47.755 --> 00:15:49.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know, but we must
make the best of it.

330
00:15:49.515 --> 00:15:52.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What are
the other five trials?

331
00:15:52.593 --> 00:15:55.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Blood, pain, sacrifice,
anguish...

332
00:15:56.326 --> 00:15:57.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and death.

333
00:15:57.152 --> 00:15:58.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sounds like marriage,
all right.

334
00:15:59.719 --> 00:15:59.952 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How would you know?

335
00:16:00.316 --> 00:16:01.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It is time to begin.

336
00:16:06.909 --> 00:16:08.829 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
QUARK:
Need more flowers on the banister.

337
00:16:08.908 --> 00:16:10.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MALE: We're ready
with the banner, boss.

338
00:16:10.508 --> 00:16:11.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>whistles </i>)

339
00:16:11.708 --> 00:16:12.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Raise it.

340
00:16:12.828 --> 00:16:14.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're up early.

341
00:16:14.587 --> 00:16:15.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought writers
slept late.

342
00:16:15.906 --> 00:16:17.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not always.

343
00:16:17.107 --> 00:16:18.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I sold my first
book today.

344
00:16:18.746 --> 00:16:21.385 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Really? How much
did you get for it?

345
00:16:21.465 --> 00:16:23.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's just a
figure of speech.

346
00:16:23.105 --> 00:16:24.504 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Federation
News Service

347
00:16:24.584 --> 00:16:26.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is going to publish
a book of my stories

348
00:16:26.144 --> 00:16:27.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
about life on the station
under Dominion rule.

349
00:16:27.423 --> 00:16:28.983 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And they're not
paying you?

350
00:16:29.626 --> 00:16:30.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

351
00:16:30.263 --> 00:16:31.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, then you have
my sympathies

352
00:16:31.982 --> 00:16:33.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the first round
of drinks is on the house.

353
00:16:33.821 --> 00:16:34.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really?

354
00:16:34.941 --> 00:16:38.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No. It's a figure
of speech.

355
00:16:38.100 --> 00:16:39.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look, I want to tell
my dad about the book.

356
00:16:39.700 --> 00:16:41.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Is he still in
the holosuite?

357
00:16:41.998 --> 00:16:43.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, yeah.
They're still up there.

358
00:16:43.898 --> 00:16:45.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are they doing?

359
00:16:45.778 --> 00:16:48.977 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's a Klingon
bachelor party.

360
00:16:50.456 --> 00:16:51.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're a writer.

361
00:16:51.656 --> 00:16:53.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Use your imagination.

362
00:16:56.214 --> 00:16:58.544 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
BASHIR:
Alexander.

363
00:16:59.294 --> 00:17:01.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Grandma?

364
00:17:01.936 --> 00:17:02.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Guess again.

365
00:17:05.971 --> 00:17:07.251 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're still on the...?

366
00:17:07.331 --> 00:17:11.170 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The road to <i>Kal'Hyah,</i>
day 500.

367
00:17:11.250 --> 00:17:13.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe we should
turn down the heat

368
00:17:13.290 --> 00:17:15.493 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you know, for
Alexander's sake.

369
00:17:15.128 --> 00:17:17.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, no, it's okay.
I, uh...

370
00:17:17.328 --> 00:17:20.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just need some water.

371
00:17:20.207 --> 00:17:22.927 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, you don't want
to push yourself too hard.

372
00:17:23.697 --> 00:17:26.606 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, turning down the heat
might be a good idea.

373
00:17:27.525 --> 00:17:29.564 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The whole point
is to push yourself

374
00:17:29.645 --> 00:17:32.204 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to the limits
of your endurance.

375
00:17:33.764 --> 00:17:35.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>panting </i>)

376
00:17:36.922 --> 00:17:38.362 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I will.

377
00:17:38.441 --> 00:17:41.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I want to travel
the entire path to <i>Kal'Hyah.</i>

378
00:17:41.601 --> 00:17:43.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stoke the fire again!

379
00:17:43.761 --> 00:17:45.640 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
As you wish.

380
00:17:45.719 --> 00:17:51.278 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Of course, we cannot expect
you non-Klingons to...

381
00:17:51.358 --> 00:17:53.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
have the same stamina
as we do.

382
00:17:53.717 --> 00:17:55.957 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you wish to quit,
no one will think

383
00:17:56.369 --> 00:17:57.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
any less of you.

384
00:17:57.316 --> 00:17:58.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Who said anything
about quitting?

385
00:17:58.956 --> 00:18:00.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not me.

386
00:18:00.795 --> 00:18:02.874 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I like the heat.

387
00:18:02.955 --> 00:18:04.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's the spirit.

388
00:18:06.673 --> 00:18:08.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>Kaaa vek ko lee ko </i>♪

389
00:18:08.833 --> 00:18:11.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>eh to che maH lo </i>♪

390
00:18:11.512 --> 00:18:16.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
♪ <i>TaH oo-wah kaH esh to</i>
<i>pah deH ah reee! </i>♪

391
00:18:16.190 --> 00:18:18.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>YaH Bosh-ah! </i>♪

392
00:18:18.870 --> 00:18:21.109 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>YaH Bosh-ah! </i>♪

393
00:18:21.189 --> 00:18:23.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>YaH Bosh tomaH! </i>♪

394
00:18:23.669 --> 00:18:24.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Al'qoch</i>

395
00:18:24.988 --> 00:18:26.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>mensaH</i>

396
00:18:26.147 --> 00:18:27.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>t'lang</i>

397
00:18:27.107 --> 00:18:28.267 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>cho.</i>

398
00:18:31.546 --> 00:18:32.786 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Again.

399
00:18:33.905 --> 00:18:36.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've done it
three times already.

400
00:18:36.225 --> 00:18:38.864 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You continue
to rush through the ceremony,

401
00:18:38.944 --> 00:18:41.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
your body
position is poor,

402
00:18:41.503 --> 00:18:43.342 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the placement
of the braziers

403
00:18:43.422 --> 00:18:46.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
on their pedestals
is sloppy.

404
00:18:49.101 --> 00:18:51.939 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know how heavy
those things are?

405
00:18:52.205 --> 00:18:54.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A Klingon woman
would not complain.

406
00:18:54.579 --> 00:18:56.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You wouldn't make
a Klingon woman

407
00:18:56.699 --> 00:18:57.778 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
do it three times in a row.

408
00:18:57.858 --> 00:18:59.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wouldn't have to.

409
00:18:59.378 --> 00:19:01.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She'd have done it correctly
the first time.

410
00:19:04.936 --> 00:19:06.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
End this now, Jadzia.

411
00:19:06.655 --> 00:19:08.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Go back to your own people.

412
00:19:09.154 --> 00:19:11.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They will tolerate
your weaknesses

413
00:19:11.454 --> 00:19:14.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and your failings
in a way that a Klingon family

414
00:19:14.254 --> 00:19:15.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
never will.

415
00:19:15.932 --> 00:19:19.332 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In our House, you would
always be an alien--

416
00:19:19.412 --> 00:19:21.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
an outsider.

417
00:19:21.571 --> 00:19:23.112 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
At best, you'd be
an object of pity

418
00:19:23.908 --> 00:19:25.249 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but you'd never
be accepted

419
00:19:25.330 --> 00:19:26.730 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
never an equal

420
00:19:26.809 --> 00:19:30.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because you can never
truly be one of us.

421
00:19:36.806 --> 00:19:39.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ko'ma tlang'goS ak-bay</i>

422
00:19:39.486 --> 00:19:43.165 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Hava'dak croosh tovaH</i>

423
00:19:43.244 --> 00:19:44.964 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ko'ma Kahless</i>

424
00:19:45.444 --> 00:19:47.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ko'ma Kahless</i>

425
00:19:47.403 --> 00:19:50.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ko'ma Kahless.</i>

426
00:19:58.559 --> 00:20:01.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But the Second Dynasty ended
when General K'Trelan

427
00:20:01.639 --> 00:20:03.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
assassinated Emperor Reclaw.

428
00:20:03.638 --> 00:20:06.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For the next ten years,
the Empire was ruled

429
00:20:06.557 --> 00:20:08.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
by a Council elected
by the people.

430
00:20:08.716 --> 00:20:10.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Modern-day
Klingon historians

431
00:20:10.916 --> 00:20:13.355 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
refer to this
as "The Dark Time."

432
00:20:13.435 --> 00:20:17.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it's interesting to note
that this first and only

433
00:20:17.634 --> 00:20:19.153 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
experiment
in Klingon democracy

434
00:20:19.234 --> 00:20:21.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
actually produced
several reforms...

435
00:20:21.753 --> 00:20:23.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You are straying from the saga.

436
00:20:23.672 --> 00:20:25.112 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Am I?

437
00:20:26.391 --> 00:20:29.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your task is to recite
the complete chronicle

438
00:20:29.990 --> 00:20:31.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
of the women in my family.

439
00:20:31.990 --> 00:20:33.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just thought I'd give you

440
00:20:33.630 --> 00:20:36.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a broader historical perspective
along the way.

441
00:20:36.349 --> 00:20:39.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I am familiar
with Klingon history.

442
00:20:39.948 --> 00:20:45.106 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, return to the story
of my 23rd maternal grandmother

443
00:20:45.186 --> 00:20:48.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Shenara,
daughter of Emperor Reclaw

444
00:20:48.145 --> 00:20:49.824 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in the Second Dynasty.

445
00:20:49.905 --> 00:20:53.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, that's where we run
into a little bit of a problem.

446
00:20:53.183 --> 00:20:55.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You see, I did some research

447
00:20:55.263 --> 00:20:57.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and when Emperor Reclaw
was killed,

448
00:20:57.502 --> 00:20:59.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
all of the members
of the Imperial Family

449
00:21:00.620 --> 00:21:02.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
