00:28:13.771 --> 00:28:15.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on.

603
00:28:18.450 --> 00:28:20.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wrong door.

604
00:28:26.647 --> 00:28:28.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excuse me, sir.

605
00:28:37.845 --> 00:28:37.964 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jadzia

606
00:28:38.443 --> 00:28:39.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
we need to...

607
00:28:43.835 --> 00:28:44.522 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're mad.

608
00:28:44.603 --> 00:28:47.241 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am concerned.

609
00:28:47.322 --> 00:28:49.241 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, well, I'm hung over.

610
00:28:49.321 --> 00:28:50.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can we talk later?

611
00:28:50.840 --> 00:28:53.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have a very
serious problem.

612
00:28:53.279 --> 00:28:55.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sirella has canceled
the wedding.

613
00:28:55.799 --> 00:28:58.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She doesn't waste
any time, does she?

614
00:28:58.558 --> 00:29:00.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She said
you attacked her.

615
00:29:01.837 --> 00:29:03.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She pulled a knife.

616
00:29:08.115 --> 00:29:10.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You are forbidden to join
the House of Martok.

617
00:29:10.794 --> 00:29:13.313 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So I won't be invited
to the family picnics.

618
00:29:13.394 --> 00:29:15.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll live.

619
00:29:15.313 --> 00:29:17.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I cannot believe
how you're taking this so lightly.

620
00:29:17.952 --> 00:29:19.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you hear that?

621
00:29:19.152 --> 00:29:20.512 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

622
00:29:20.591 --> 00:29:21.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>muffled voices </i>)

623
00:29:21.991 --> 00:29:23.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It sounds like voices.

624
00:29:29.349 --> 00:29:30.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Hi.
-Hi.

625
00:29:30.748 --> 00:29:32.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
ODO:
Is the party over?

626
00:29:32.828 --> 00:29:36.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You could say that.
It's 10:30.

627
00:29:36.227 --> 00:29:38.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In the morning?
I'm on duty.

628
00:29:38.706 --> 00:29:40.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So am I.

629
00:29:40.266 --> 00:29:41.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was a great party.

630
00:29:41.385 --> 00:29:42.545 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks.

631
00:29:49.383 --> 00:29:51.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We must deal
with the situation now.

632
00:29:51.342 --> 00:29:54.662 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Stop yelling.
My head hurts.

633
00:29:54.741 --> 00:29:57.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You must go to Sirella
and beg her forgiveness.

634
00:30:04.618 --> 00:30:06.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't beg.

635
00:30:06.457 --> 00:30:09.937 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You are allowing
your pride to blind you.

636
00:30:10.175 --> 00:30:11.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Look who's talking.

637
00:30:11.496 --> 00:30:13.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You want me to go crawling
to some old hag

638
00:30:13.296 --> 00:30:15.295 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
just so you can have your
traditional Klingon wedding.

639
00:30:15.375 --> 00:30:17.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is about more
than just tradition.

640
00:30:20.134 --> 00:30:23.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You and I have embarked
on a spiritual journey,

641
00:30:23.453 --> 00:30:24.852 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
one that will
bind us together

642
00:30:24.932 --> 00:30:26.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
through this life
and into the next.

643
00:30:27.124 --> 00:30:28.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You cannot turn back now.

644
00:30:28.691 --> 00:30:31.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe you're on
a spiritual journey, Worf,

645
00:30:31.210 --> 00:30:33.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I just want
to get married.

646
00:30:33.170 --> 00:30:36.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So why don't you go back
to sweating and bleeding

647
00:30:36.729 --> 00:30:38.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
with your friends
in the holosuite,

648
00:30:38.488 --> 00:30:39.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and when you're done,

649
00:30:39.888 --> 00:30:41.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
meet me in
Benjamin's office

650
00:30:41.607 --> 00:30:43.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and he'll perform
the ceremony.

651
00:30:51.125 --> 00:30:53.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If that is your attitude...

652
00:30:55.443 --> 00:30:57.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
perhaps Sirella
was right about you.

653
00:31:00.602 --> 00:31:02.881 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There should be no wedding.

654
00:31:04.806 --> 00:31:05.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's fine with me.

655
00:31:08.639 --> 00:31:10.719 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>door opens, closes </i>)

656
00:31:24.674 --> 00:31:28.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>whistling </i>)

657
00:31:28.673 --> 00:31:29.952 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's going on?

658
00:31:30.331 --> 00:31:30.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Haven't you heard?

659
00:31:31.724 --> 00:31:32.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The wedding's off.

660
00:31:32.152 --> 00:31:33.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Off? Why?

661
00:31:33.872 --> 00:31:38.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She says it's because
he's a pig-headed, stubborn man

662
00:31:38.550 --> 00:31:40.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who puts tradition
before everything else.

663
00:31:40.989 --> 00:31:43.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He says it's because
she's a frivolous

664
00:31:43.388 --> 00:31:44.828 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
emotional woman

665
00:31:44.908 --> 00:31:47.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who refuses to take him
or his culture seriously.

666
00:31:47.267 --> 00:31:49.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can see
the problem.

667
00:31:49.467 --> 00:31:50.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're both right.

668
00:31:51.270 --> 00:31:52.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Exactly.

669
00:31:52.306 --> 00:31:55.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well... there's only
one thing for it.

670
00:31:56.625 --> 00:31:58.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dinner.

671
00:31:58.744 --> 00:32:00.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll get the menu.

672
00:32:08.581 --> 00:32:10.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>door chimes </i>)

673
00:32:10.101 --> 00:32:11.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Enter.

674
00:32:18.218 --> 00:32:20.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Worf...

675
00:32:20.378 --> 00:32:22.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you've made a grave error.

676
00:32:24.497 --> 00:32:27.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perhaps.

677
00:32:27.256 --> 00:32:29.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you still love her?

678
00:32:29.495 --> 00:32:31.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course.

679
00:32:31.534 --> 00:32:34.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
However, in this
case, <i>that...</i>

680
00:32:34.494 --> 00:32:36.373 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
may not be enough.

681
00:32:38.452 --> 00:32:41.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Anyone can see that we are
hopelessly mismatched.

682
00:32:41.411 --> 00:32:43.490 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She is a Trill;
I am a Klingon.

683
00:32:43.571 --> 00:32:46.130 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She has had
five marriages.

684
00:32:46.210 --> 00:32:48.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This would be my first.

685
00:32:48.409 --> 00:32:51.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When she is laughing,
I am somber.

686
00:32:51.288 --> 00:32:53.881 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When I am happy,
she is crying.

687
00:32:53.168 --> 00:32:56.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She plays <i>tongo </i>with
the Ferengi bartender.

688
00:32:56.206 --> 00:32:58.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can barely stand him.

689
00:33:00.485 --> 00:33:03.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She mocks everything...

690
00:33:03.324 --> 00:33:05.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
while I take
everything seriously.

691
00:33:08.403 --> 00:33:10.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She is nothing like the woman
I thought I would marry.

692
00:33:13.201 --> 00:33:15.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We are not accorded
the luxury

693
00:33:15.521 --> 00:33:18.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of choosing the women
we fall in love with.

694
00:33:18.920 --> 00:33:21.639 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you think Sirella
is anything like the woman

695
00:33:21.719 --> 00:33:23.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought that I'd marry?

696
00:33:25.198 --> 00:33:29.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She is a prideful,
arrogant, mercurial woman

697
00:33:30.768 --> 00:33:34.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who shares my bed far too
infrequently for my taste.

698
00:33:35.755 --> 00:33:37.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And yet...

699
00:33:39.234 --> 00:33:41.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I love her...

700
00:33:41.513 --> 00:33:43.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
deeply.

701
00:33:43.512 --> 00:33:45.312 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hmm.

702
00:33:45.392 --> 00:33:49.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We Klingons often tout our...

703
00:33:49.670 --> 00:33:51.670 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
prowess in battle...

704
00:33:51.750 --> 00:33:56.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
our desire for glory and honor
above all else...

705
00:33:56.869 --> 00:34:00.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but how hollow is
the sound of victory...

706
00:34:00.188 --> 00:34:03.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
without someone
to share it with?

707
00:34:03.147 --> 00:34:06.146 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Honor gives
little comfort

708
00:34:06.226 --> 00:34:08.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to a man alone
in his home...

709
00:34:08.265 --> 00:34:10.784 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and in his heart.

710
00:34:16.343 --> 00:34:17.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
One steak with mushrooms

711
00:34:18.231 --> 00:34:19.622 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
baked potato, sour cream
and chives.

712
00:34:19.701 --> 00:34:21.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I should have had that.

713
00:34:21.182 --> 00:34:24.301 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
One double Altair sandwich,
no mustard...

714
00:34:24.380 --> 00:34:26.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
two bowls of linguini,

715
00:34:26.180 --> 00:34:29.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bajoran shrimp
with extra cheese.

716
00:34:29.996 --> 00:34:31.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
One loaf of mapa bread.

717
00:34:31.618 --> 00:34:33.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Quark, where's
the <i>kava </i>juice?

718
00:34:33.417 --> 00:34:34.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're still
squeezing the roots

719
00:34:34.577 --> 00:34:35.977 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
unless you want replicated.

720
00:34:36.572 --> 00:34:37.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We'll wait.

721
00:34:37.416 --> 00:34:39.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
SISKO:
What do you think you're doing?

722
00:34:40.255 --> 00:34:41.295 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The wedding's
been called off.

723
00:34:41.375 --> 00:34:42.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's back on.

724
00:34:42.535 --> 00:34:44.974 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Worf is apologizing
to Jadzia

725
00:34:45.542 --> 00:34:46.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
at this very moment.

726
00:34:46.334 --> 00:34:47.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Quark, take
it all away.

727
00:34:47.894 --> 00:34:50.532 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No food for those
on the path to <i>Kal'Hyah.</i>

728
00:34:50.613 --> 00:34:53.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No refunds for those on the path
to <i>Kal'Hyah </i>as well.

729
00:34:53.532 --> 00:34:54.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry.

730
00:34:59.410 --> 00:35:01.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Father, what happened?

731
00:35:03.929 --> 00:35:05.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She refused
to change her mind

732
00:35:05.808 --> 00:35:07.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and the wedding is still off.

733
00:35:07.887 --> 00:35:09.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

734
00:35:09.873 --> 00:35:10.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where is she?

735
00:35:10.166 --> 00:35:12.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In her quarters.

736
00:35:12.126 --> 00:35:14.165 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll go talk to her.

737
00:35:14.246 --> 00:35:17.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just... keep them away
from the food?

738
00:35:24.203 --> 00:35:25.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>door chimes </i>)

739
00:35:25.282 --> 00:35:26.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come in!

740
00:35:28.281 --> 00:35:29.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Save your breath.

741
00:35:29.521 --> 00:35:31.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Worf's gone too far,
and now it's over.

742
00:35:31.800 --> 00:35:33.759 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you know what
he wanted me to do?

743
00:35:33.840 --> 00:35:36.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He wanted me to go crawling
on my hands and knees to Sirella

744
00:35:36.999 --> 00:35:38.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to beg her forgiveness.

745
00:35:38.518 --> 00:35:39.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Beg her! Me!

746
00:35:39.917 --> 00:35:41.518 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was once

747
00:35:41.597 --> 00:35:44.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the Federation Ambassador
to the Klingon Empire.

748
00:35:46.676 --> 00:35:48.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I negotiated
the Khitomer Accords

749
00:35:48.595 --> 00:35:49.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
before Worf
was even born.

750
00:35:50.347 --> 00:35:51.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Curzon negotiated the Accords!

751
00:35:52.749 --> 00:35:53.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I've got news for you,
old man.

752
00:35:53.514 --> 00:35:55.113 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're not Curzon anymore.

753
00:35:55.193 --> 00:35:57.352 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And what the hell is that
supposed to mean?

754
00:35:57.433 --> 00:35:59.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It means that you
can't expect Sirella

755
00:35:59.272 --> 00:36:00.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to treat you like Curzon

756
00:36:00.511 --> 00:36:02.711 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
just because you carry
his memories.

757
00:36:02.790 --> 00:36:04.151 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
To her, you're just
a young woman

758
00:36:04.230 --> 00:36:06.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who decided to marry
into her family.

759
00:36:06.430 --> 00:36:07.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If it means
you have to bow down

760
00:36:07.909 --> 00:36:09.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and kiss her boots,

761
00:36:09.508 --> 00:36:12.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that's exactly what you have
to do, and you knew that.

762
00:36:12.668 --> 00:36:14.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The moment you decided
to marry Worf,

763
00:36:14.947 --> 00:36:17.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you knew that sooner or later
you'd have to bow down

764
00:36:17.147 --> 00:36:19.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and show her the respect
that she's due.

765
00:36:19.746 --> 00:36:21.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is Worf's fault--

766
00:36:21.345 --> 00:36:23.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Worf and his traditional
Klingon wedding.

767
00:36:23.944 --> 00:36:26.646 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, he may have let
this wedding business

768
00:36:26.144 --> 00:36:30.636 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
go to his head,
but you are 356 years old.

769
00:36:30.143 --> 00:36:32.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Compared to you,
Worf is just a kid.

770
00:36:32.982 --> 00:36:35.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And if you can't abide
by Klingon traditions,

771
00:36:35.981 --> 00:36:37.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
then you never should
have let yourself

772
00:36:37.461 --> 00:36:39.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
fall in love with him
in the first place.

773
00:36:41.819 --> 00:36:44.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And you <i>are</i>
in love with him.

774
00:36:47.338 --> 00:36:49.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wasn't looking
to fall in love.

775
00:36:49.257 --> 00:36:52.256 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was perfectly happy
by myself.

776
00:36:52.336 --> 00:36:55.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I had friends, a career,
adventure...

777
00:36:58.174 --> 00:37:01.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then one day...

778
00:37:01.373 --> 00:37:03.972 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
this Klingon
with a bad attitude

779
00:37:04.533 --> 00:37:05.492 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
walked into my life

780
00:37:05.572 --> 00:37:09.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the next thing I know,
I'm getting married.

781
00:37:09.731 --> 00:37:13.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
After 356 years
and seven lifetimes...

782
00:37:15.129 --> 00:37:17.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I still lead with my heart.

783
00:37:17.648 --> 00:37:20.928 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, that is
what I've always loved about you.

784
00:37:23.767 --> 00:37:26.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I think that's why
Worf loves you, too.

785
00:37:32.164 --> 00:37:35.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

786
00:37:35.123 --> 00:37:41.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Whatever happened to that
young, callow Ensign I used to know?

787
00:37:41.482 --> 00:37:43.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The one who used
to turn to me

788
00:37:43.921 --> 00:37:45.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for advice all the time?

789
00:37:46.400 --> 00:37:49.759 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know,
the one with hair?

790
00:37:49.839 --> 00:37:51.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I grew up.

791
00:37:55.757 --> 00:37:58.636 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I guess it's time
I grow up, too.

792
00:37:58.716 --> 00:38:00.595 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mmm.

793
00:38:39.624 --> 00:38:41.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
With fire and steel

794
00:38:41.863 --> 00:38:45.222 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
did the gods forge
the Klingon heart.

795
00:38:45.302 --> 00:38:46.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So fiercely did it beat,

796
00:38:47.618 --> 00:38:50.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so loud was the sound,
that the gods cried out,

797
00:38:50.861 --> 00:38:53.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"On this day
we have brought forth

798
00:38:53.820 --> 00:38:57.218 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"the strongest heart
in all the heavens.

799
00:38:57.299 --> 00:39:00.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"None can stand before it
without trembling

800
00:39:00.617 --> 00:39:01.977 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
at its strength."

801
00:39:02.577 --> 00:39:05.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But then the Klingon heart
weakened

802
00:39:05.416 --> 00:39:07.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
its steady rhythm faltered
and the gods said,

803
00:39:07.976 --> 00:39:10.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Why have you weakened so?

804
00:39:10.135 --> 00:39:11.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"We have made you the strongest

805
00:39:11.614 --> 00:39:14.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in all of creation."

806
00:39:14.533 --> 00:39:16.253 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And the heart said...

807
00:39:16.333 --> 00:39:17.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am alone.

808
00:39:19.452 --> 00:39:21.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And the gods knew
that they had erred.

809
00:39:21.611 --> 00:39:23.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So they went back
to their forge

810
00:39:23.451 --> 00:39:26.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and brought forth...
another heart.

811
00:39:54.442 --> 00:39:58.640 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But the second heart
beat stronger than the first,

812
00:39:58.721 --> 00:40:00.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the first was jealous
of its power.

813
00:40:05.518 --> 00:40:07.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fortunately...

814
00:40:07.277 --> 00:40:08.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the second heart
was tempered

815
00:40:08.717 --> 00:40:10.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
by wisdom.

816
00:40:10.237 --> 00:40:13.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If we join together,
no force can stop us.

817
00:40:20.993 --> 00:40:24.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And when the two hearts
began to beat together,

818
00:40:24.272 --> 00:40:28.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
they filled the heavens
with a terrible sound.

819
00:40:28.111 --> 00:40:31.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For the first time,
the gods knew fear.

820
00:40:31.911 --> 00:40:34.709 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They tried to flee,
but it was too late.

821
00:40:34.790 --> 00:40:37.828 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Klingon hearts
destroyed the gods

822
00:40:37.909 --> 00:40:39.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
who created them

823
00:40:39.148 --> 00:40:42.227 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and turned the heavens
to ashes.

824
00:40:42.307 --> 00:40:43.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
To this very day

825
00:40:44.671 --> 00:40:48.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
no one can oppose the beating
of two Klingon hearts.

826
00:40:51.264 --> 00:40:52.584 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not even me.

827
00:40:56.783 --> 00:41:00.702 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Worf, son of Mogh,
does your heart beat

828
00:41:00.782 --> 00:41:02.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
only for this woman?

829
00:41:02.941 --> 00:41:04.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes.

830
00:41:04.980 --> 00:41:07.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And will you swear
to join with her

831
00:41:07.979 --> 00:41:10.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and stand with her
against all who oppose you?

832
00:41:11.589 --> 00:41:13.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I swear.

833
00:41:13.578 --> 00:41:16.137 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jadzia, daughter of Kela,

834
00:41:16.217 --> 00:41:19.816 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
does your heart beat
only for this man?

835
00:41:19.896 --> 00:41:21.816 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes.

836
00:41:21.895 --> 00:41:23.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And do you swear
to join with him

837
00:41:24.548 --> 00:41:25.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and stand with him

838
00:41:25.375 --> 00:41:26.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
against all
who would oppose you?

839
00:41:28.374 --> 00:41:29.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
( <i>whispering </i>):
I swear.

840
00:41:31.133 --> 00:41:33.532 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then let all present
here today know

841
00:41:33.611 --> 00:41:38.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that this man
and this woman are married.

842
00:41:38.210 --> 00:41:40.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>applause </i>)

843
00:41:45.568 --> 00:41:46.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now?

844
00:41:47.477 --> 00:41:48.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not yet.

845
00:41:55.765 --> 00:41:56.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now?

846
00:41:56.725 --> 00:41:58.604 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Patience.

847
00:42:00.643 --> 00:42:02.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My Lady.

848
00:42:03.642 --> 00:42:05.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Welcome to the House
of Martok...

849
00:42:07.241 --> 00:42:08.881 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
my daughter.

850
00:42:13.200 --> 00:42:14.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now, Doctor!

851
00:42:14.759 --> 00:42:17.358 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( <i>yelling </i>)

